    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just hard to shake the feeling that we're all just wasting time. like, we spend our whole lives building these elaborate mental and physical structures, just to have them dissolved by physics eventually. if nothing we do leaves a permanent impact, then why bother with the struggle of staying alive? it just seems like a massive, exhausting loop that leads nowhere.",
