      "content": "i guess. but \"embracing the futility\" still requires you to keep going through the motions, which feels pretty heavy. if the whole thing is just an accident and it's all going to end in nothing anyway, why is there this intense pressure to just keep enduring the pain and the effort? it feels like we're being forced to participate in a game that's rigged to be meaningless.",
